00:12:45.958 --> 00:12:49.500
Oh. how-how-how could you not know
who the Bee Gees are? The Bee Gees.

252
00:12:51.458 --> 00:12:52.667
Where's Crosby?

253
00:12:55.625 --> 00:12:56.875
Crosby?

254
00:12:57.792 --> 00:13:00.226
-Oh. God. Crosby. No. Come on.
-Oh. oh. oh. oh! Oh. shit!

255
00:13:00.250 --> 00:13:04.333
Wake up. little buddy. Wake up. boy.
What's happened? What's he eaten?

256
00:13:06.375 --> 00:13:09.333
Fucking hell. Alice.
You did the course. Do mouth-to-mouth.

257
00:13:10.708 --> 00:13:13.668
-Come on. do it! Mouth-to-mouth!
-I'm doing it! I'm doing it! I'm doing it!

258
00:13:15.500 --> 00:13:18.292
Okay. Uh. tell me exactly
what Crosby ingested.

259
00:13:24.125 --> 00:13:26.417
Pills. uh. for my heart.
I h… I have a heart condition.

260
00:13:27.042 --> 00:13:28.125
And what pills?

261
00:13:30.167 --> 00:13:31.500
Can you tell me specifically?

262
00:13:32.208 --> 00:13:33.583
Hmm…

263
00:13:33.667 --> 00:13:35.907
If I give Crosby the wrong medication.
it could kill him.

264
00:13:35.958 --> 00:13:37.333
-He ate cocaine.
-By accident.

265
00:13:37.417 --> 00:13:38.625
It may have been off.

266
00:13:42.875 --> 00:13:44.500
Bogna's a really pretty name.

267
00:13:47.875 --> 00:13:48.875
What if they arrest us?

268
00:13:50.833 --> 00:13:54.208
We could say it wasn't our coke.
It was just on the floor.

269
00:13:55.083 --> 00:13:57.583
I would rather go to jail than Crosby die.

270
00:14:02.750 --> 00:14:06.917
Dogs can't eat chocolate. onion.
grapes or class A drugs.

271
00:14:07.000 --> 00:14:08.792
You need to be more careful in future.

272
00:14:09.458 --> 00:14:11.917
I've given him some Diazepam
and there are a few extras here

273
00:14:12.000 --> 00:14:14.208
to give him if he gets
distressed in the night.

274
00:14:14.292 --> 00:14:15.292
Thank you.

275
00:14:16.625 --> 00:14:18.750
I'm-I'm so. so sorry.

276
00:14:18.833 --> 00:14:22.292
It's okay. It's fine.
you can't have known that would happen.

277
00:14:24.167 --> 00:14:26.250
Is one of Crosby's eyes
bigger than the other?

278
00:14:30.625 --> 00:14:31.833
Don't laugh. it's not funny.

279
00:14:32.417 --> 00:14:33.500
I know. I know.

280
00:14:34.333 --> 00:14:35.958
Have a look.

281
00:14:36.042 --> 00:14:38.083
No. it's the sa… It's the same.

282
00:14:38.750 --> 00:14:39.750
I'm so sorry.

283
00:14:42.667 --> 00:14:45.208
It's okay. boy. It's okay.

284
00:14:45.292 --> 00:14:47.667
Maybe we should both have
one of Crosby's diazepams.

285
00:14:49.208 --> 00:14:51.500
I'm… Oh. I'm joking.

286
00:14:51.583 --> 00:14:52.583
Give them to me.

287
00:14:58.375 --> 00:15:00.125
-You need anything else?
-No.

288
00:15:00.208 --> 00:15:03.250
Okay well. I'll be up for ages.
so if you need anything.

289
00:15:03.333 --> 00:15:06.250
anything at all.
even if Crosby's just upset.

290
00:15:06.333 --> 00:15:07.833
you… you just come and get me.

291
00:15:07.917 --> 00:15:08.958
Okay.

292
00:15:09.542 --> 00:15:11.125
Okay?

293
00:15:12.542 --> 00:15:14.542
I'm right here if you need me.

294
00:15:29.083 --> 00:15:30.708
-Hello. Oh…
-Fuck!

295
00:15:30.792 --> 00:15:32.333
-…sorry.
-You scared…

296
00:15:32.417 --> 00:15:33.792
I didn't see you. Sorry…

297
00:15:33.875 --> 00:15:36.708
-Sorry. Steve here. obviously. Uh…
-Yeah.

298
00:15:36.792 --> 00:15:40.292
Yeah. your mum said I could stay.
It's been a bit… bit of a big night.

299
00:15:40.375 --> 00:15:42.250
Why are you under the duvet like that?

300
00:15:42.333 --> 00:15:44.708
Uh… Yeah. fair question.

301
00:15:44.792 --> 00:15:49.625
Um. I noticed very briefly that. uh.

302
00:15:49.708 --> 00:15:52.000
you're not wearing trousers. so I. uh…

303
00:15:52.083 --> 00:15:54.208
-Oh.
-So I thought this would be less awkward.

304
00:15:54.292 --> 00:15:55.917
-but it… but it feels…
-Yeah.

305
00:15:56.000 --> 00:15:57.000
Yeah. maybe it isn't.

306
00:15:57.083 --> 00:15:59.167
Okay. well. it's all right.
Don't worry about it.

307
00:15:59.250 --> 00:16:02.125
I was just getting another drink.
Do you want one?

308
00:16:04.125 --> 00:16:05.125
Yes. please.

309
00:16:11.000 --> 00:16:15.542
So. how bad was your day from one to ten?

310
00:16:17.833 --> 00:16:19.458
Uh. it was a strong eight.

311
00:16:19.542 --> 00:16:20.583
-Oof.
-What about yours?

312
00:16:20.667 --> 00:16:21.958
Uh. yeah.

313
00:16:22.750 --> 00:16:25.458
Yeah. eight seems about right.

314
00:16:29.750 --> 00:16:30.750
Thank you.

315
00:16:44.625 --> 00:16:46.667
So. why did Nancy break up with you?

316
00:16:46.750 --> 00:16:52.458
Oh. God.
Um. okay. well. yeah. let's discuss this.

317
00:16:54.125 --> 00:16:57.125
Apparently. um. I didn't do anything.

318
00:16:57.208 --> 00:17:01.667
as in I only reacted
and also I was a lazy fucker.

319
00:17:01.750 --> 00:17:04.750
According to her. her words. not mine.

320
00:17:04.833 --> 00:17:06.875
Now. what… …what about you?

321
00:17:07.500 --> 00:17:12.167
Um. he said that I was too emotional…

322
00:17:12.250 --> 00:17:13.958
-Mm-hmm.
-…and that…

323
00:17:14.042 --> 00:17:16.833
That I said "sorry"
and "I love you" too much.

324
00:17:16.917 --> 00:17:17.958
What a shit you are.

325
00:17:18.042 --> 00:17:19.167
I know.

326
00:17:19.250 --> 00:17:20.309
How could you do that to him?

327
00:17:20.333 --> 00:17:25.208
Yeah. And the sad thing is.
I didn't even really mean it.

328
00:17:25.292 --> 00:17:28.208
-Mm-hmm.
-Like. I was just pretending to be nice

329
00:17:28.292 --> 00:17:31.208
and hiding all my dark shit.

330
00:17:31.292 --> 00:17:35.125
Clever move.
I do that too. Definitely wanna hide that.

331
00:17:37.417 --> 00:17:39.833
What was the final thing
that pushed him over?

332
00:17:40.375 --> 00:17:44.667
I think I was talking about my wedding?

333
00:17:45.250 --> 00:17:47.917
Oh. Were you… Were you guys engaged?

334
00:17:48.667 --> 00:17:52.000
No. No. um.
I didn't even imagine him being there.

335
00:17:52.083 --> 00:17:54.101
It was mostly just thinking about
the dress and the hair.

336
00:17:54.125 --> 00:17:55.667
Who were you marrying?

337
00:17:55.750 --> 00:17:58.542
No. really I was just thinking about
the dress and the hair.

338
00:17:59.125 --> 00:18:02.792
Well if…
if you ever need a stylist.

339
00:18:02.875 --> 00:18:05.083
Free. totally free.

340
00:18:11.208 --> 00:18:12.667
I can't believe you're single.

341
00:18:15.750 --> 00:18:17.167
If you'd seen me earlier tonight.

342
00:18:17.250 --> 00:18:20.583
you would absolutely believe
I'm single and will always be single.

343
00:18:22.500 --> 00:18:26.375
I just… I hadn't noticed it before.
but you are weirdly hot.

344
00:18:27.125 --> 00:18:28.208
Thank you.

345
00:18:28.292 --> 00:18:29.292
Yeah.

346
00:18:32.458 --> 00:18:36.292
Not sure about the use of
the word "weirdly" though.

347
00:18:36.375 --> 00:18:37.667
-We… Weirdly.
-Yeah.

348
00:18:39.042 --> 00:18:40.833
M-Maybe you have a weird smell?

349
00:18:41.375 --> 00:18:43.667
-Probably.
-Apparently it's all about smells.

350
00:18:45.125 --> 00:18:46.125
Mmm.

351
00:18:59.792 --> 00:19:01.559
-You smell really nice.
-Thank you. thank you.

352
00:19:01.583 --> 00:19:03.750
That's nice.

353
00:19:09.875 --> 00:19:11.333
Do I smell nice?

354
00:19:16.583 --> 00:19:18.542
Mmm.

355
00:19:44.708 --> 00:19:46.625
He never usually leaves this early.

356
00:19:50.458 --> 00:19:52.125
I can't bear it if he's angry with me.

357
00:19:52.208 --> 00:19:54.917
What? Why… Why would he be angry with you?

358
00:19:58.375 --> 00:20:04.000
I left my bag on the floor
and Crosby ate something out of it.

359
00:20:04.083 --> 00:20:05.750
Oh.

360
00:20:05.833 --> 00:20:07.208
No. I don't think so.

361
00:20:07.292 --> 00:20:09.458
I saw Crosby last night.
seemed completely fine.

362
00:20:10.292 --> 00:20:13.875
And uh. Steve's probably
just a bit rattled. about Mike.

363
00:20:13.958 --> 00:20:15.333
and the funeral and stuff.

364
00:20:15.417 --> 00:20:18.750
You're right.
Of course you're right.

365
00:20:18.833 --> 00:20:21.750
Ooh.

366
00:20:21.833 --> 00:20:24.042
No.

367
00:20:24.125 --> 00:20:27.542
I love that you're home.

368
00:20:27.625 --> 00:20:29.875
Is it… Is it selfish that I'm so happy
that you're back?

369
00:20:29.958 --> 00:20:31.458
-Yes!
-Yeah. you're right.

370
00:20:31.542 --> 00:20:33.375
-Of course it is. Sorry.
-It's horrible.

371
00:20:33.458 --> 00:20:35.083
Am I allowed to go and kill Janis now?

372
00:20:35.167 --> 00:20:36.167
No.

373
00:20:38.125 --> 00:20:40.500
You do know I'd kill for you. don't you?

374
00:20:41.333 --> 00:20:45.375
I'd happily smoosh his smug little face.

375
00:20:47.333 --> 00:20:48.667
Ooh. maybe that's Steve!

376
00:20:49.375 --> 00:20:50.708
Whoo. whoo. whoo. whoo!

377
00:20:55.167 --> 00:20:57.042
Oh. Hi.

378
00:20:57.958 --> 00:20:59.667
I'm Rome.

379
00:20:59.750 --> 00:21:01.250
-Hey.
-Hi.

380
00:21:01.333 --> 00:21:06.792
Oh! You're Dom's friend. Come in. Come in.

381
00:21:06.875 --> 00:21:09.375
Um. my mum gets overly excited.

382
00:21:09.458 --> 00:21:11.338
So I'd stick to yes or no answers
if I were you.

383
00:21:11.417 --> 00:21:14.208
And if she starts dancing then look away.

384
00:21:20.500 --> 00:21:24.958
Rome. would you be angry with me
if I'd almost killed your dog?

385
00:21:27.792 --> 00:21:28.833
Yes.

386
00:21:32.708 --> 00:21:33.792
I'm gonna call Steve.

387
00:21:44.875 --> 00:21:47.167
Hey. this is Steve Wild.
please leave a message.

388
00:21:47.250 --> 00:21:49.500
Okay. call me.

389
00:21:49.583 --> 00:21:51.417
I'm-I'm worried that you were tired

390
00:21:51.500 --> 00:21:54.042
and you pulled a towel too hard
from your linen closet

391
00:21:54.125 --> 00:21:55.645
and you've been crushed underneath it.

392
00:21:55.708 --> 00:21:57.042
Please don't hate me.

393
00:21:57.125 --> 00:21:59.167
Love you! Okay. bye!

394
00:21:59.250 --> 00:22:01.458
Hey. this is Steve Wild.
please leave a message.

395
00:22:01.542 --> 00:22:03.833
Okay. it's been over two days.

396
00:22:03.917 --> 00:22:07.375
And now I'm worried that you're dead.
Can you just text me to say you're alive?

397
00:22:07.458 --> 00:22:13.042
Love you.
I love you. Goodbye.

398
00:22:18.167 --> 00:22:21.500
♪ Yes. I love you ♪

399
00:22:21.583 --> 00:22:23.375
♪ And you trust me? ♪

400
00:22:25.417 --> 00:22:28.250
♪ I'm not sure ♪

401
00:22:32.333 --> 00:22:36.500
♪ Oh. you don't know me ♪

402
00:22:36.583 --> 00:22:38.500
♪ You can trust me ♪

403
00:22:40.042 --> 00:22:42.458
♪ I don't know ♪

404
00:22:48.917 --> 00:22:49.917
Oh.

405
00:22:50.875 --> 00:22:52.583
Why are you not answering your phone?

406
00:22:54.542 --> 00:22:55.976
I-I know I shouldn't have come here.

407
00:22:56.000 --> 00:22:59.875
but I'm-I'm finding it surprisingly hard
to stop thinking about you.

408
00:23:00.875 --> 00:23:02.583
I'm sorry. I-I should never have…

409
00:23:02.667 --> 00:23:04.458
Oh. don't apologise.

410
00:23:04.542 --> 00:23:08.208
I mean. that was…
that was excellent sex. Was it not?

411
00:23:09.458 --> 00:23:11.375
Did… Did you like it?

412
00:23:12.583 --> 00:23:13.583
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

413
00:23:13.667 --> 00:23:14.667
Very much.

414
00:23:14.750 --> 00:23:15.750
Okay.

415
00:23:16.250 --> 00:23:18.917
Very much. but as good as it was. uh.

416
00:23:19.000 --> 00:23:21.750
-we-we can… we can never do it again.
-No. yeah.

417
00:23:22.375 --> 00:23:25.792
You're probably right. You're right.

418
00:23:25.875 --> 00:23:26.875
Yeah.

419
00:23:27.708 --> 00:23:29.583
Good. Good.

420
00:23:29.667 --> 00:23:30.667
Yeah.

421
00:23:31.833 --> 00:23:32.833
Mmm.

422
00:23:34.250 --> 00:23:35.290
It was really good though…

423
00:23:35.333 --> 00:23:37.417
-Oh. my God. It was so good.
-Wasn't it? So good.

424
00:23:37.500 --> 00:23:41.125
Some of those things
I had never. ever tried before.

425
00:23:41.208 --> 00:23:43.167
-But we can't do that to my mum…
-No. No. no. no.

426
00:23:43.250 --> 00:23:45.375
-I'm not saying we keep doing it…
-We can't do…

427
00:23:45.458 --> 00:23:47.101
-…I was just replaying it in my head…
-Yeah.

428
00:23:47.125 --> 00:23:48.645
-…a little bit…
-Because of Mum. right.

429
00:23:48.708 --> 00:23:51.292
But we can't do it
because your mum's my best friend.

430
00:23:51.375 --> 00:23:53.417
So we never tell her.

431
00:23:53.500 --> 00:23:57.208
Oh. no. No. no.
No. I don't… Definitely not.

432
00:23:57.292 --> 00:24:00.292
-Mm-hmm.
-Yes. Def… I mean. yes. no. we can't.

433
00:24:00.833 --> 00:24:02.042
We definitely can't tell her.

434
00:24:02.625 --> 00:24:04.083
Just out of interest.

435
00:24:04.167 --> 00:24:07.167
if I wasn't her daughter.
would you have asked me out?

436
00:24:12.708 --> 00:24:13.708
Yeah.

437
00:24:14.542 --> 00:24:20.917
Okay. Okay.
Where… Where would you have taken me?

438
00:24:21.500 --> 00:24:22.583
To eat food.

439
00:24:23.583 --> 00:24:25.583
-I love eating food.
-Do you?

440
00:24:25.667 --> 00:24:26.875
We have so much in common.

441
00:24:26.958 --> 00:24:29.809
That's one of the things you would've
experienced. but unfortunately you can't.

442
00:24:29.833 --> 00:24:31.708
-So…
-Well. what's your favourite food?

443
00:24:31.792 --> 00:24:33.875
Italian. Spaghetti vongole.

444
00:24:33.958 --> 00:24:36.167
-I love spaghetti vongole.
-Really?

445
00:24:36.250 --> 00:24:37.792
Yes. Favourite song?

446
00:24:38.958 --> 00:24:41.083
You won't even know the song.
you're too young.

447
00:24:41.625 --> 00:24:43.250
But it always makes me cry.

448
00:24:43.333 --> 00:24:45.750
"Blue Skies". Willie Nelson.

449
00:24:46.500 --> 00:24:49.583
♪ Blue skies. shining at me ♪

450
00:24:50.375 --> 00:24:55.875
♪ Nothing but blue skies do I see ♪

451
00:25:01.875 --> 00:25:04.583
Tell me something
I won't like about you. Quick!

452
00:25:04.667 --> 00:25:06.143
-I hate swimming.
-I hate swimming too.

453
00:25:06.167 --> 00:25:07.917
-So that's no good.
-I don't like football.

454
00:25:08.000 --> 00:25:09.417
I loathe it. I hate the cold.

455
00:25:09.500 --> 00:25:11.726
I don't like the cold either.
Who likes the cold? It's too cold.

456
00:25:11.750 --> 00:25:13.809
Well. I don't particularly like
being too hot either.

457
00:25:13.833 --> 00:25:15.792
Ah. well. I like the heat.

458
00:25:17.208 --> 00:25:19.375
-So we're not compatible.
-Yeah. no.

459
00:25:20.458 --> 00:25:22.292
That's good. that's good.

460
00:25:28.917 --> 00:25:30.833
The… Someone's at the door.

461
00:25:33.542 --> 00:25:34.667
Are you sure?

462
00:25:35.833 --> 00:25:36.875
Yes.

463
00:25:38.750 --> 00:25:42.667
You should go open the door.
You should open it. Go.

464
00:25:44.042 --> 00:25:45.417
-Go.
-I'm going.

465
00:25:53.292 --> 00:25:54.833
I'm very cross with you.

466
00:25:55.625 --> 00:25:59.750
Now let me in.
Because I come bearing gifts.

467
00:26:02.167 --> 00:26:05.250
Um… Why don't we go for a walk?

468
00:26:05.333 --> 00:26:06.333
-Leave these here…
-What?

469
00:26:06.417 --> 00:26:08.351
-And we'll go for a nice walk.
-What do you mean? Walk?

470
00:26:08.375 --> 00:26:09.583
No. no walk.

471
00:26:09.667 --> 00:26:11.059
-Come on. fire up the telly…
-Alice…

472
00:26:11.083 --> 00:26:13.123
I've got clothes for Crosby.
wait till you see them.

473
00:26:14.167 --> 00:26:16.583
I've got treats for you both.

474
00:26:16.667 --> 00:26:18.167
Wait. wait. wait. wait. wait.

475
00:26:18.250 --> 00:26:21.917
Ah. ah. ah. ah. ah. look.

476
00:26:22.000 --> 00:26:23.000
Aw…

477
00:26:23.667 --> 00:26:24.750
What are you doing here?

478
00:26:26.625 --> 00:26:30.583
Are you trying to fix our fight?

479
00:26:31.292 --> 00:26:34.542
Oh. darling. oh. that's so sweet.

480
00:26:35.167 --> 00:26:37.417
But we're fine. Aren't we? We're fine.

481
00:26:37.500 --> 00:26:40.208
Mmm. Mm-hmm.

482
00:26:40.292 --> 00:26:41.500
I slept with Steve.

483
00:26:46.958 --> 00:26:47.958
Sorry?

484
00:26:48.458 --> 00:26:49.708
We. um…

485
00:26:50.875 --> 00:26:53.625
We slept together the night
that Steve stayed over at ours.

486
00:26:54.750 --> 00:26:56.542
But it's not what you think.

487
00:26:57.292 --> 00:27:00.417
I like him.
I actually really. really like him.

488
00:27:00.500 --> 00:27:02.750
And I think he might like me.

489
00:27:04.417 --> 00:27:07.417
And I know this must hurt. Mum.
I see that.

490
00:27:08.333 --> 00:27:11.042
But I want to keep seeing him.

491
00:27:16.792 --> 00:27:20.542
Oh. that's really funny. Um…

492
00:27:32.875 --> 00:27:39.542
♪ Silver and sunshine
That's what our love is made of ♪

493
00:27:39.625 --> 00:27:45.292
♪ So precious and bright
How wonderful is our love ♪

494
00:27:46.750 --> 00:27:52.958
♪ Cherries and roses
That's what our hearts believe in ♪

495
00:27:53.042 --> 00:27:59.542
♪ So sweet and so white
How wonderful is our love ♪

496
00:27:59.625 --> 00:28:06.417
♪ In these dark and angry times
When all the laws fall through ♪

496
